    27	**Optimal K:** K = sqrt(x / log^3 x) → total O(sqrt(x) * polylog(x)).
    28	
    29	**Enhancement:** If we additionally know p(n) mod M for some modulus M, the effective sieve width shrinks to W/M, giving O(x^{1/2-epsilon} * polylog) if M = x^epsilon.
