    0	# Prime Research: Computing p(n) Exactly Without Bruteforcing
    1	
    2	## Goal
    3	Find an O(polylog) algorithm to compute the nth prime p(n) exactly.
    4	Target: p(10^100) in <1 second, 100% accurate.
    5	
    6	## Status (April 2026)
    7	- **575+ approaches tested** across 24 sessions, 160+ sub-agents
    8	- **All known paths closed** but no proof that polylog is impossible
    9	- **Problem is genuinely open** -- no unconditional lower bound beyond Omega(log x)
    10	- **Proving impossibility faces Natural Proofs barrier** -- as hard as P != NP (S23)
    11	- Best exact: `algorithms/v10_c_accelerated.py` -- O(p(n)^{2/3}), p(10^9) in 0.175s
    12	- Best approximate: R^{-1}(n) -- O(polylog), ~50% digits correct
    13	
    14	## The Barrier (One Paragraph)
