## Critique Session Complete

### Results

**All 16 Session 26 proposals: DUPLICATE.** Every proposal maps to existing CLOSED_PATHS entries from Sessions 1-25. Session 26 was self-consistent (it generated and closed its own proposals), so this critique confirms correctness rather than finding new flaws.

### One New Experiment

The **group-theoretic prime race shortcut** — the only untested suggestion from Session 26b's synthesis — was experimentally tested and **CLOSED**:
- Cross-modulus correlations are trend artifacts (roughness ratio 0.997 after detrending)
- Galois lifts go in the wrong direction (fine→coarse free, coarse→fine needs new zeros)
- Linear prediction of p(n) mod q from E(x;q_i): R² < 0.03
- CRT via prime races costs 96 L-functions, each O(sqrt(x)) = strictly worse

