    19	---
    20	
    21	## PROPOSAL 1: Spectral Truncation + Sieve Hybrid
    22	
    23	### Mathematical Idea
    24	Use K zeta zeros in the truncated explicit formula to narrow pi(x) to an interval of width W ~ x/K, then sieve that interval for primes.
    25	
    26	**Cost:** O(K * polylog(x) + W * log log W) where W = x/K.  
    27	**Optimal K:** K = sqrt(x / log^3 x) → total O(sqrt(x) * polylog(x)).
    28	
    29	**Enhancement:** If we additionally know p(n) mod M for some modulus M, the effective sieve width shrinks to W/M, giving O(x^{1/2-epsilon} * polylog) if M = x^epsilon.
