    ECCC TR26-008 observes that recent works on trapdoored matrices by Vaikuntanathan and Zamir (SODA 2026) and Braverman and Newman (TCC 2025) imply that, assuming strong but plausible cryptographic assumptions, natural proofs cannot establish circuit lower bounds higher than n·polylog(n) for linear functions A:F^n→F^n.
    
    The paper addresses the fundamental long-standing open problem of proving super-linear lower bounds on the size of circuits computing explicit linear functions A:F^n→F^n in circuit complexity. The focus is on the case where F is a finite field.
    
    The report was published on January 20, 2026, and the authors include Ran Raz and others.
    
    
