| Entropy of p(n) mod q | Exactly maximum | Zero exploitable modular structure |
| Low-rank of zero matrix | 99% energy at rank 119/200 | Not compressible |

### The three barriers, now empirically confirmed
1. **Information**: ~log(x)/2 bits from zeros, maximum entropy, no compression
2. **Sieve**: x^{2/3} is the optimal combinatorial tradeoff
3. **Analytic**: Zero sum is GUE-random in fine structure, K(x) ~ x^{0.47}

### Literature: Nothing changes the picture
Most interesting new tools: ANTEDB (automated exponent optimization) and FBQPOLYLOG (quantum polylog complexity class characterization). Neither provides a path to polylog prime counting.

