**Hierarchical sieve agent** -- the final agent -- confirms: **All 5 approaches FAIL**.

Key insight: **The Fast Multipole Method analogy fails because prime sieving has no "far field"** -- small primes create periodic patterns spanning the full range uniformly. Modular arithmetic is intrinsically global.

Notable finding: truncated inclusion-exclusion at x=10000 only needs |S|≤5 terms (1396 out of 2^25 possible), but this is because products of 6+ small primes exceed x. At x=10^100, essentially all 2^{pi(10^50)} terms are nonzero.

