    21	## PROPOSAL 1: Sparse Fourier Transform on the Explicit Formula
    22	
    23	### Mathematical Idea
    24	The Riemann explicit formula pi(x) = R(x) - sum_rho R(x^rho) is a sum over zeta zero contributions. Each contribution oscillates with frequency gamma_k * ln(x). If this signal is "effectively sparse," the Sparse Fourier Transform (Hassanieh et al. 2012) can recover dominant components in O(k * polylog(N)) time.
